description:
the first album by the group Thug Life, started by rapper Tupac Shakur, and was released on September 26, 1994. The album was originally released by Shakur's label Out Da Gutta Records. Due to heavy criticism on gangsta rap at the time, the original version of the album was scrapped and re-recorded with many of the original songs being cut. It has been said that 2Pac created two other versions of this album, with many of the songs still remaining unreleased.
The group featured Big Syke, Macadoshis, Mopreme, The Rated R and Tupac Shakur. Among the notable tracks on the album are &quot;Bury Me a G,&quot; &quot;Cradle to the Grave,&quot; &quot;Pour Out a Little Liquor&quot; (which also appears in the soundtrack to the 1994 film Above the Rim), &quot;How Long Will They Mourn Me?&quot; and &quot;Str8 Ballin'.&quot;


Track listing:


1&quot;Bury Me a G&quot; (feat. Natasha Walker)	

2&quot;Don't Get It Twisted&quot;	

3&quot;Shit Don't Stop&quot; (feat. Y.N.V.)

4&quot;Pour Out a Little Liquor&quot;	

5&quot;Stay True&quot; (feat. Stretch)	

6&quot;How Long Will They Mourn Me?&quot; (feat. Nate Dogg)

7&quot;Under Pressure&quot; (feat. Stretch)	

8&quot;Street Fame&quot;	

9&quot;Cradle to the Grave&quot;	

10&quot;Str8 Ballin'&quot;

The album only contains ten tracks because Interscope records felt many of the other recorded songs were too controversial to release.
